The paper deals with the problem of universal compression of sequences from a mixture of parametric sources, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The use of side information is a common technique in machine learning and data analysis, which suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). The clustering technique presented in the paper is a method commonly used in data science and data analysis, which suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The use of real network data traces in the simulations suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of multimedia (cs.MM) or social and information networks (cs.SI).
